Feat: Add reward model data rebalancing and batch hard-negative synthesis

The initial reward model trained on raw preference pairs exhibited severe
language bias (inflated scores for Chinese/English regardless of humor
quality), caused by data imbalance (~0.7% Chinese in ~151K total pairs).

This commit introduces a two-pronged rebalancing strategy plus batch API
optimization for the hard-negative synthesis pipeline:

1. Per-language downsampling: format_reward_pairs() now accepts
   max_pairs_per_lang (default 10K) to cap over-represented languages.
2. Hard-negative synthesis: new synthesize_reward_data.py generates
   preference pairs with real jokes as chosen and Gemini-generated
   boring text as rejected, with pre-extracted CFun CSV as Chinese
   positive source (rule-filtered: dedup + length 10-500).
3. Batch Gemini API calls: _call_gemini_batch() uses structured JSON
   output (response_mime_type + response_json_schema) to generate 100
   items per API call, reducing total calls by ~10x and cutting
   synthesis time from ~22 min to ~2 min for 9K samples.

Detailed Changes:
1. data_preprocessing/formatters.py: Add max_pairs_per_lang and
   synthesized_reward_dir parameters to format_reward_pairs(). Implement
   per-language downsampling and synthesized pair merging logic.
2. data_preprocessing/synthesize_reward_data.py: New script for reward
   hard-negative synthesis.
   - Chinese chosen loaded from local data/cfun/pure_jokes.csv with
     rule-based filtering (dedup, length 10-500).
   - EN/ES chosen from unified_all.jsonl high-score jokes.
   - Rejected generated via Gemini API in batches of 100 using
     structured JSON output (_call_gemini_batch), replacing the previous
     one-at-a-time _call_gemini approach.
   - Assembles TRL-compatible preference pairs {prompt, chosen, rejected}.
3. data_preprocessing/pipeline.py: Update run_format_reward() to pass
   rebalancing parameters. Add --max_pairs_per_lang CLI argument.
4. data_preprocessing/visulization.ipynb: Add preference pair language
   distribution statistics and sample inspection section.
5. data_preprocessing/DATA_PIPELINE_DESIGN.md: Update architecture diagram,
   add language rebalancing strategy (Section 6.5), hard-negative synthesis
   pipeline with CSV rule-based filtering (Section 6.6), new file
   organization and pipeline commands.
6. tests/test_formatters.py: Unit tests for downsampling and synthesized
   data merging in format_reward_pairs().
7. tests/test_synthesize_reward_data.py: Unit tests for CSV-based CFun
   loading (dedup, length filter, file not found, empty after filter),
   high-score joke loading, preference pair assembly, boring text quality
   filtering, batch API call parsing/retry logic, and generate_boring_texts
   batch orchestration (early stop, multi-batch, filter passthrough).
